        "body": "Summary\r\n\r\nImplements a complete classical NLP machine learning pipeline to classify legal contract clauses as **Risky (1)** or **Safe (0)** using scikit-learn.\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n### New Package – `src/model_training/`\r\n| File | Description |\r\n|------|-------------|\r\n| `config.py` | Central constants: `TEST_SIZE`, `RANDOM_STATE`, output paths |\r\n| `data_loader.py` | Validates DataFrame schema and returns a stratified 80/20 train/test split |\r\n| `feature_extractor.py` | `TfidfVectorizer` with unigram + bigram features and sublinear TF scaling |\r\n| `trainer.py` | Trains `LogisticRegression` and `DecisionTreeClassifier` (both with `class_weight=\"balanced\"`) |\r\n| `evaluator.py` | Prints `classification_report` (precision / recall / F1) for each model; selects best by macro F1 |\r\n| `model_saver.py` | Persists best model + vectorizer to `models/` via `joblib.dump` |\r\n\r\n### New Entry-Point\r\n- **`train_classifier.py`** – Orchestrates the full pipeline end-to-end. Replace `build_demo_dataframe()` with your real data source.\r\n\r\n### Supporting Changes\r\n- `requirements.txt` – Added `joblib==1.3.2`\r\n- `.gitignore` – Excludes `.venv/`, `__pycache__/`, and `models/`\r\n\r\n## How to Run\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npython3 train_classifier.py\r\n",
